The paper deals with speech separation using deep clustering and unsupervised deep learning methods, which are primarily related to speech processing and machine learning. Therefore, cs.SD (Sound) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) are the most likely categories. The paper also involves the use of multilayer bootstrap networks, which is a novel unsupervised deep learning method, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a likely category as well. Finally, the paper deals with speaker-independent speech separation, which falls under the category of cs.SI (Speech Recognition and Synthesis).
